Patch Set 6:

Changes looks promising to me and good progress on first attempt itself. I just want to be sure how we are going to treat this.

Bug or New feature?

Depending on we need either Launchpad bug or glance lite-specs to go ahead.

Patch Set 6:

> Changes looks promising to me and good progress on first attempt
 > itself. I just want to be sure how we are going to treat this.
 > 
 > Bug or New feature?
 > 
 > Depending on we need either Launchpad bug or glance lite-specs to
 > go ahead.

I feel like it's really hard (irresponsible event) to consider wsgi_app to be something that is in the tree, has been the default deployment mechanism in devstack for years, same for OSA, yet is completely unsupported. Major clouds deploy it that way, so IMHO, this is just a bug fix to address the problem with tasks, etc.

Patch Set 6:

From a stable team perspective, I'm good with this being considered a bugfix and backporting it to open stable branches. It touches a lot of code, but as Dan says, this is something that has been expected for some time now and it really would be good to do whatever we can to make Glance not be the one odd outlier.
